    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Distinctive vessels in certain Protestant churches that are used to contain monetary offerings by the congregation; usually having a slotted lid. Vases of this type were formerly used to contain notes for those receiving communion.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
